<HEADLINE>
<P>
EWALD T. GRETHER; FOUNDING DEAN OF UC BERKELEY BUSINESS SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ewald T. Grether, 94, founding dean of the University of California at 
Berkeley's business school.Grether, who was dean from 1941 to 1961, was a 
consultant to three U.S. presidents and an adviser to California Gov. Earl 
Warren on water resources development, employment and unemployment insurance 
and industrial development. Grether reorganized the school's college of 
commerce, which was established in 1898, into the School of Business 
Administration, the predecessor of the Haas School of Business. He retired in 
1961 and died in Berkeley on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
