<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS; MARTIN AND LENDL OUSTED FROM FLORIDA TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Todd Martin and Ivan Lendl were eliminated in third-set tiebreakers in the 
second round of the Lipton Championships at Key Biscayne, Fla., on Sunday, but 
top-seeded Pete Sampras and Steffi Graf both won easily. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin, who will play for the U.S. Davis Cup team at India in two weeks, lost 
to Byron Black of Zimbabwe, 4-6, 6-2, 7-6 (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
 A finalist at the Australian Open, Martin continued his recent slump by losing 
for the third time in five matches. The American, ranked ninth in the world, 
said he is weary from already playing in six tournaments this year. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think I just need a few days off, and hopefully I'll get the energy back in 
my legs and in my head," Martin said. "I'll just do something other than run 
around on a piece of cement." 
</P>
<P>
 Lendl, meanwhile, squandered two match points, including one on a disputed 
call, and lost to Jan Siemerink of the Netherlands, 3-6, 7-5, 7-6 (7-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Sampras, the defending champion, ousted Diego Nargiso, 6-2, 6-2, and 
fourth-seeded Jim Courier rallied to defeat Jeff Tarango of Manhattan Beach, 
2-6, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Spain's Javier Sanchez defeated his older brother Emilio, 3-6, 6-2, 6-4, for 
his first victory in eight matches this year and his first in 10 against 
Emilio. 
</P>
<P>
 In women's play, Graf defeated Ginger Helgeson, 6-2, 6-1, for her 28th 
consecutive victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Second-seeded Aranxta Sanchez Vicario, the two-time defending champion, 
defeated Patty Fendick, 6-1, 6-3, and third-seeded Gabriela Sabatini eliminated 
Chanda Rubin, 6-3, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
