<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES IN 2ND FATAL SKI ACCIDENT IN 2 DAYS AT HEAVENLY VALLEY RESORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 31-year-old man has become the second person in two days to die in a ski 
accident at Heavenly Valley Ski Resort. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado County sheriff's deputies said the man, whose name was withheld 
pending notification of relatives, was skiing fast down Rusutsu Run when he 
struck a tree early Sunday afternoon.He died of massive head injuries about an 
hour later at a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 He was the fourth fatality this season in Lake Tahoe ski accidents -- all at 
Heavenly Valley. All four died after hitting trees. 
</P>
<P>
 The man died one day after an exchange student from Scotland was killed when 
he went out of control on Lower Ellie's Run. Garry David Rogers, 18, who had 
been attending high school in Healdsburg, suffered massive head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are certainly asking questions about why four fatalities could happen in 
one season," Heavenly Valley spokesman John Wagnon said. "It's very odd to have 
four fatalities in a season, let alone two on the same weekend." 
</P>
</TEXT>
