<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; FLORIDA; $884 MILLION SPENT ON ILLEGAL IMMIGRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State and local governments spent $884 million last year on health care, 
education, prisons and other public services for 345,000 illegal immigrants, a 
new report says.The report will be used to support a lawsuit Gov. Lawton Chiles 
plans to file against the federal government seeking reimbursement for services 
to refugees and illegal immigrants. The report, "The Unfair Burden: 
Immigration's Impact on Florida," is the first attempt by state officials to 
put a price on the services used by legal and illegal aliens. It was prepared 
by the governor's office and the Florida Advisory Council on Intergovernmental 
Relations. 
