<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; HILTON D. BELL SCHOOL TO MARK ITS 25TH YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hilton D. Bell Intermediate School will celebrate its 25th anniversary this 
week. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-day tribute, starting today, will recognize those who attended or 
worked at the campus since it opened. Festivities will include campus 
decorations, an after-school dance and a 1960s dress-up day for students, said 
Alan Trudell of the Garden Grove Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 An anniversary dinner will be held Tuesday in the multipurpose room at the 
campus, 12345 Springdale St. The dinner will start at 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 663-6466. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
