<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; CAMP FOR DISABLED YOUTHS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By E.J. GONG JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A weeklong sports camp for disabled youths begins March 29 at Saddleback 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which is free for youngsters between 7 and 18 years old, is the 
14th annual camp sponsored by the National Foundation of Wheelchair Tennis. 
</P>
<P>
 The camp will provide instruction for beginners and the more advanced in 
tennis, basketball, track and field, archery, aquatics, road racing and 
physical conditioning. 
</P>
<P>
 Camp officials said the program is designed for those who have good use of 
their upper bodies and possess self-help skills. 
</P>
<P>
 All the athletic instructors are disabled athletes and will serve as both 
counselors and role models for the campers, according to camp officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The daily camp hours will be from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m., and a free lunch is 
included. Free bus transportation to and from the camp is also provided. 
</P>
<P>
 To enroll a child or sponsor a camper, call (714) 361-6811. Camp applications 
are due by Tuesday. E.J. GONG JR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
