<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 'SEEING GREEN' SERIES OFFERED THIS MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Dunes Resort has planned a series of activities this month to 
celebrate awareness of the Earth's environment. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Seeing Green" series will continue Friday with a bicycle tour through the 
Back Bay area conducted by a naturalist. On March 26, there will be free nature 
walks through the wildlife preserve. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Orange Coast College and the Newport Dunes Resort will co-sponsor a 
recycling program to fund student scholarships to the college. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 729-3863. ROBERT ELSTON 
</P>
