<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 3 YOUTHS TAKE TOP HONORS AT ART SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Ventura County children have been honored as winners of a regional art 
show sponsored by the Boys & Girls Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Shull of Ojai, and Crystal Jack and Leonardo Martinez, both of 
Ventura, earned first place last week in their respective age groups in the 
sculpture category. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian won in the 9 and under category for his sculpture titled "Here's 
Looking at You, Ducky," said Pat Borison, a club spokeswoman. Crystal came out 
on top in the 10-12 age group for her "Fancy Flower" sculpture, and Leonardo 
placed first in the 13-15 division for his work titled "Breakfast a la 
Leonardo." 
</P>
<P>
 Their work will be among 36 entries to be sent on to the Boys & Girls Club 
national headquarters in Atlanta for a national competition next month. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 700 pieces of art by Boys & Girls Club members from nine Western 
states were submitted for the exhibit. Judging took place Wednesday at the Boys 
& Girls Club on Johnson Drive in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners' sculptures, plus works submitted by members of Boys & Girls clubs 
in Camarillo, Oxnard, Simi Valley, Moorpark and Ventura, will be included in an 
exhibit set to start this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibit will be open Thursday to March 27 from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. at 
Ventura Harbor Village, 1583 Spinnaker Drive. Boys & Girls Club officials hold 
the competition each year to encourage members to develop artistic talents, 
Borison said. 
</P>
<P>
 Local clubs conduct year-round art classes, crafts demonstrations and special 
arts activities, she said. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</TEXT>
