<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; REWARD OFFERED FOR TIPS IN CAR 
BREAK-INS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENDA DAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Crime Stoppers Program is offering up to $1,000 for 
information leading to the arrest of thieves who stole air bags and stereos 
from BMWs in a Thousand Oaks auto dealer's lot last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The cars were parked at the Rusnak BMW dealership when thieves smashed the 
windows of 11 cars between Tuesday night and Wednesday morning, police 
said.Five of the cars belonged to customers who had dropped them off for 
repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 The thieves removed air bag assemblies from the steering wheels of eight cars 
and took the Alpine or Pioneer stereos from 10. The loss totaled $26,000, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information should contact Crime Stoppers at 494-TALK in Thousand 
Oaks and Moorpark, 987-TALK in Camarillo, 385-TALK in Oxnard or 986-TALK in 
Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 Callers may remain anonymous and will be assigned a number as their only 
identification to authorities. If the information leads to an arrest with a 
criminal complaint filed, the caller will be eligible for the reward. BRENDA 
DAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
