WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; KIDNAPING REPORTED BY WOMAN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man forced his way into an Oxnard woman's car while she was stopped at a 
Ventura intersection and made her to drive him to the San Fernando Valley, 
Ventura police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 32-year-old woman told investigators that she was stopped at a traffic 
light at Wake Forest Avenue and Telegraph Road about noon Saturday when an 
unknown man opened her passenger-side door and sat next to her. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect, whose description was not provided by police, then ordered the 
woman to drive south on the Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 A police spokeswoman said the man told the woman to exit at Reseda Boulevard, 
then he jumped out of the car. At no time did he display a weapon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 She then returned home and called police at 8:15 p.m. Saturday. The case is 
being investigated as a felony kidnaping. JEFF McDONALD 
