<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAGUNA HILLS TOURNAMENT TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The second full week of softball play begins today at Alicia Park in Mission 
Viejo with the Laguna Hills tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Some of the county's best teams are taking part, including Marina, the 
defending Sunset League champion; Woodbridge and Irvine, which shared the Sea 
View League title; Empire League champion Foothill, and Pacific Coast League 
champion Laguna Hills, which won the Division III title in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight first-round games will be played tonight, including the most attractive 
matchup, El Toro-Fountain Valley, at 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament continues nightly, with the winners playing at 7 p.m. 
throughout the four-day tournament. The championship will be decided at 7:15 
p.m. Thursday. MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
