<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Premier Sets Modest Growth Target of 9%: Li Peng has set the cautious target 
for 1994, declaring that stability cannot be sacrificed for short-term economic 
gains.Rising inflation, economic bottlenecks and a flood of corruption washing 
across the country could undermine China's achievements and tip the country 
into turmoil, Li said. He said the 9% target for gross domestic product growth 
this year represents a reasonable slowing from the 13.4% China recorded in 1993 
and should prove to be a sustainable pace for several years. Inflation must be 
held below 10% and new investment strictly controlled to prevent another sudden 
expansion of credit, Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031494-0177 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 022754 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
