<DATE>
<P>
March 14, 1994, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 3; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
55 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Machine Tool Orders Off Sharply: Orders tumbled 11.6% in January from a year 
ago and fell 5.2% from the previous month to $361.68 million, the Japan Machine 
Tool Builders Assn said. Orders to machine tool builders are considered a 
leading economic indicator because machine tools are used to make equipment for 
manufacturers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
