<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Southwest Chamber Music Society has received $20,000 from the Clarence E. 
Heller Charitable Foundation in San Francisco to fund rehearsal of all 17 of 
Beethoven's string quartets, to be played in the fall of 1995. The Society's 
next concert, a program of Schoenberg and Luigi Nono, will be given March 27 at 
4 p.m. in Bertea Hall at Chapman University in Orange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
